						<p>
						This is a place to find no-background-knowledge-required explanations of
						code libraries and software.

						<br><br>
						<em>Why?</em>
						Because every time I dive into a new area, I re-experience the pain of having
						to learn the lingo before being able to understand what the simplest things are.

						<br><br>
						When you google "YAML", the most prominent
						result comes from Wikipedia. It explains that "YAML is a human-readable
						data-serialization language." Those intimidating, obscure words
						"data-serialization language" kept me from looking any
						further for 5 years. When I finally gathered the courage to dive into
						the explanation, I found out that YAML is just a
						standardized format for storing data, similar to JSON.

						<br><br>
						Simple explanations of most technical concepts are possible.
						I hope that WIF can give them a home.

